------
<a name="antichess"></a>
#### Antichess

In <a  href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Losing_Chess'> antichess </a> the objective is to <i>lose</i> all your peaces (or reach a stalemate).

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_antichess.js"
    id="17fdfa5d-d806-44bf-afab-34fd9723ffc8"
    data-bokeh-model-id="6909e13c-cf6a-4584-992a-0a23f47f47ea"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="6f3aa140-a093-4c12-93d7-1dc85c2f6300"
></script>
</center>
</div>

The number of games played per month of *antichess* - the second most popular chess variant on lichess - increases steadily. In march, **154723** games were played!

------
<a name="atomic"></a>
#### Atomic


In <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_chess'> atomic chess </a> captures result in a nuclear explosion destroying all surrounding pieces -  except pawns.

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_atomic.js"
    id="7ff36197-1463-43e8-b8d8-3c3b47002f7f"
    data-bokeh-model-id="ba0bab12-a254-492f-adae-ecafa622267b"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="83edba13-56b2-480f-bc27-f4ec84ac3709"
></script>
</center>
</div>


*Atomic chess* had its peak in february but is still gaining robustly in popularity.

------
<a name="chess960"></a>
#### Chess960

In <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess960'> Chess960 </a> the starting position of the pieces on both players' home ranks is randomized (*960* is the number of possible starting formations).

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_chess960.js"
    id="87d881ce-7633-4ca7-abcf-4a6591e23eac"
    data-bokeh-model-id="b37bef08-1fb3-47fe-a3b9-e8348f430bd2"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="7bae4299-334a-49ca-9ed9-1ffbdb9c1744"
></script>
</center>
</div>

Also, more and more played is *Chess960*. What a beautiful increase, right?

------
<a name="crazyhouse"></a>
#### Crazyhouse

[Crazyhouse](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crazyhouse) allows players to introduce captured pieces back to the board as their *own*. Crazy, right?

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_crazyhouse.js"
    id="6e71fa72-ca90-440e-a815-124a792da6de"
    data-bokeh-model-id="98bd75ed-0677-4017-9264-a7f073fa9829"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="d902c909-8fb2-4b05-9292-a08d98cd58bb"
></script>
</center>
</div>

While crazyhouse had its peak in march (**183112** games), it's popularity isn't increasing that much.
Still, it's the most popular chess variant on lichess!

------
<a name="horde"></a>
#### Horde

In the [horde](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dunsany%27s_Chess) chess variant a horde of  (32!) bloodthirsty pawns has to be defeated.

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_horde.js"
    id="27923c6c-7a01-43a1-a38f-b1cb36ace64f"
    data-bokeh-model-id="c210cf1a-cf9f-4185-a4eb-fd5d9eefe69e"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="99618ace-fff3-4d6a-82a6-8a8bff01b60b"
></script>
</center>
</div>

Despite being scary, it's also getting more popular!

------
<a name="kingofthehill"></a>
#### King of the hill

In *King of the hill* a player is victorious if she moves her king to one of the central four squares (or in case of the usual checkmate).

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_kingofthehill.js"
    id="baf4dcb6-394d-4350-88c4-54fc7210f392"
    data-bokeh-model-id="9dfc4604-a22f-4e23-b915-05d0e2b2da3f"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="dcc1014b-a241-453a-94a0-fa7264d51cfe"
></script>
</center>
</div>

*King of the hill* seems to get played less lately. Do you know why?

------
<a name="racingkings"></a>
#### Racing Kings

To win this chess variant you must race your king to the eighth rank
(<small>a pure psychological and physical torture for the poor slow king.</small>)
<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_racingkings.js"
    id="63f0e314-08a6-4630-ab7f-5ceea3ca3e54"
    data-bokeh-model-id="0cbc76ef-0e4d-4cba-ba5e-858cb1ec5c7e"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="b324a552-7ed7-43fe-ab0c-faf9f6917c8f"
></script>
</center>
</div>

While it started rather strong, *racing kings* has become the least popular chess variant.

I think people have tortured this poor little king enough anyways...

------
<a name="threecheck"></a>
#### Three-Check

In [three-check chess](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three-check_chess) the player wins who first checks his opponent's king three times.

<div>
<center>
<script
    src="bar_threecheck.js"
    id="bc873bd7-c6f6-454b-bdc2-8b374319bfa2"
    data-bokeh-model-id="8488f7bb-5a6b-4412-b185-2d7fc55e4c3b"
    data-bokeh-doc-id="624cfd61-c94c-4553-9035-54ff7cdff55b"
></script>
</center>
</div>

Who can explain the peak number of games played in january?

